I just want to say that Jasmine, who is one of your supervisors/managers at this location, is an outstanding young woman and a great employee. I ordered Blaze via Postmates, and Postmates cancelled on me - an hour and 10 minutes after I ordered and it was confirmed - and you guys had already made the food. Ridiculous.  I’m so glad I called Blaze to find out if it was the restaurant or Postmates who messed my order up. Jasmine took my phone call, and informed me my food was sitting there ready and never picked up. She offered to remake my food so it’d be hot while I called Postmates to try to get them to send another courier. Postmates is a hot mess - they would not help me. So now I feel terrible Blaze is making my order a second time and no one can pick it up for me.  Jasmine said if they weren’t so busy she’d personally deliver my food to me at work, but it’s a Friday night. Bless her heart.  I managed to leave work to go pick up the food she remade for me due to Postmates’ error and lack of good customer service. Jasmine turned the situation around for me, and she was super pleasant and accommodating.  Blaze and Jasmine have excellent customer service, and Postmates could learn a thing or two from them.  Also - this location’s food is always great when I get it. I just won’t be using Postmates to get my pizza fix anymore from here.  Thank you, Jasmine, and Blaze Pizza. Y’all rock! :-)

We had an impromptu little bday celebration for me with my 4 yr grandson. The staff, the owner, our server were all fantastic. We sat upstairs and had the most enjoyable experience. Oh yes...the pizza....outstanding.  As were our appetizer meatballs. Roberts has the feel of a local neighborhood restaurant with just the right touch of a modern sophisticated vibe. A very difficult combination to pull off indeed. And did I mention how gracious and accommodating Roberts was to a rambunctious 4 year old little boy?  I can't compliment the experience enough. I will be a regular from here on out.

What a mess. Obviously either understaffed, untrained, poorly managed, or a combination of all three. A Thursday night about 8, not particularly busy but the line is moving at a snail's pace...about 15 minutes into the line the EMT in front of me abandons the line and leaves. My order for two pizzas is eventually taken and when I get to the register one of my pizzas is out of the oven fully cooked and the other is still on the counter waiting to go in. The woman manning the register is also cooking the pizza but it's doing neither one well. The guy assembling the pizzas is now shoving them in the oven as there is no more room on the counter but there are only two in the oven. As the pizza count in the oven mounts to 7 or 8, two burn and need to be remade and recooked. Mercifully, my second pizza is not one of the burned ones. The pizzas themselves weren't bad but the experience is not one that I will repeat. I was probably there an hour, seriously. Btw... the three workers were so far behind that no one was doing any cleaning. Bad enough that the dining area was becoming a mess but far worse that the floor in front of the oven was covered with food. It's a hot mess at Blaze Pizza.
